    "content": "<p>Manufacturers supply a zener diode with zener voltage $\\mathrm{V}_{\\mathrm{z}}=5.6 \\mathrm{~V}$ and maximum power dissipation $P_{\\mathrm{z}, \\max }=\\frac{1}{4} \\mathrm{~W}$. This zener diode is used in the following circuit. Calculate the minimum value of the resistance $R_s$ in the circuit so that the zener diode will not burn when the input voltage is $\\mathrm{V}_{\\mathrm{in}}=10 \\mathrm{~V}$.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mabxe8ni/d3c9beb0-daa2-4e31-94d1-4b7397137ade/c9ce26e0-2a26-11f0-bcfd-ab15dbf11e1e/file-jaoe38c1mabxe8nj.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mabxe8ni/d3c9beb0-daa2-4e31-94d1-4b7397137ade/c9ce26e0-2a26-11f0-bcfd-ab15dbf11e1e/file-jaoe38c1mabxe8nj.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"WB JEE 2025 Physics - Electronic Devices Question 2 English\"></p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": " $98.56 \\Omega$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": " $170 \\cdot 52 \\Omega$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": " $306 \\cdot 21 \\Omega$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": " $412.37 \\Omega$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mh7xdlfp/cff3eff9-7a55-4cc8-8206-d8a8041bf23a/18ecef50-b289-11f0-929a-ef42a21afe94/file-jaoe38c1mh7xdlfq.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mh7xdlfp/cff3eff9-7a55-4cc8-8206-d8a8041bf23a/18ecef50-b289-11f0-929a-ef42a21afe94/file-jaoe38c1mh7xdlfq.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"WB JEE 2025 Physics - Electronic Devices Question 2 English Explanation\"><p>We have,</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{gathered} P=V_z I_z \\Rightarrow \\frac{1}{4}=5.6 \\times I_z \\\\ I_z=\\frac{1}{4 \\times 5.6} \\end{gathered} $$</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Also,&nbsp;&nbsp;$$ I_z=I_s $$</p>\n<p>Now, $V_s=I_s R_s \\Rightarrow R_s=\\frac{V_s}{I_s}$</p>\n<p>$$ \\Rightarrow \\quad R_s=4.4 \\times 4 \\times 5.6=98.56 \\Omega $$</p>",
