    "content": "<p>A $$2 \\mathrm{~V}$$ cell is connected across the points $$\\mathrm{A}$$ and $$\\mathrm{B}$$ as shown in the figure. Assume that the resistance of each diode is zero in forward bias and infinity in reverse bias. The current supplied by the cell is</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lwu7xg1z/2ae99072-6ad4-4362-b686-d121347e701b/0f92b970-1f0b-11ef-9623-514f9a23e0fd/file-1lwu7xg20.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lwu7xg1z/2ae99072-6ad4-4362-b686-d121347e701b/0f92b970-1f0b-11ef-9623-514f9a23e0fd/file-1lwu7xg20.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"WB JEE 2024 Physics - Electronic Devices Question 4 English\"></p>",
