    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lrihb6vp/c2766dbe-eaf5-45e5-8031-3848b0b5e808/4349fc50-b599-11ee-88fe-93f7151820af/file-6y3zli1lrihb6vq.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lrihb6vp/c2766dbe-eaf5-45e5-8031-3848b0b5e808/4349fc50-b599-11ee-88fe-93f7151820af/file-6y3zli1lrihb6vq.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"WB JEE 2023 Physics - Electronic Devices Question 7 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>The current through the circuit is</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n&amp; I=\\frac{9}{200+100}=\\frac{3}{100} \\mathrm{~A} \\\\\n\\therefore \\quad &amp; V_L=I \\cdot R_L=\\frac{3}{100} \\times 100=3 \\mathrm{~V}\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p>As $$V_L&lt; V_Z$$. So, the Zener diode will not activate and $$V_L=3 \\mathrm{~V}$$.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "wb-jee-2023",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lh5pcp18/8354915c-dfd0-401f-bf4d-ac84fc189632/5bec4fc0-e898-11ed-8179-292e62481b94/file-1lh5pcp19.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lh5pcp18/8354915c-dfd0-401f-bf4d-ac84fc189632/5bec4fc0-e898-11ed-8179-292e62481b94/file-1lh5pcp19.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2023 Physics - Electronic Devices Question 6 English\"></p>\n<p>Consider the logic circuit with inputs A, B, C and output Y. How many combinations of A, B and C gives the output Y = 0 ?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "8"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "5"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "7"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "1"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lrihidz6/f5c046d0-068b-48d8-9b33-3d1cda89f7ec/0b6f5220-b59a-11ee-88fe-93f7151820af/file-6y3zli1lrihidz7.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lrihidz6/f5c046d0-068b-48d8-9b33-3d1cda89f7ec/0b6f5220-b59a-11ee-88fe-93f7151820af/file-6y3zli1lrihidz7.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"WB JEE 2023 Physics - Electronic Devices Question 6 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>The output, $$Y=\\overline{\\overline{\\bar{A} \\cdot B}+\\bar{C}}$$</p>\n<p>Let $$D=\\bar{A} \\cdot B$$</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n&amp; \\therefore \\quad Y=\\overline{\\bar{D}+\\bar{C}}=\\overline{\\overline{D \\cdot C}}=D \\cdot C=\\bar{A} \\cdot B \\cdot C \\\\\n&amp; \\therefore \\quad Y=\\bar{A} \\cdot B \\cdot C\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p>This is AND gate with input $$\\bar{A}, B$$ and $$C$$</p>\n<p>For $$Y=1 ; \\bar{A}=1, B=1, C=1 \\Rightarrow$$ one combination.</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ The combination of $$A, B$$ and $$C$$ which gives $$Y=0$$ is</p>\n<p>$$2^n-1=2^3-1=7$$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "wb-jee-2023",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>A Zener diode having break down voltage Vz = 6V is used in a voltage regulator circuit as shown in the figure. The minimum current required to pass through the Zener to act as a voltage regulator is 10 mA and maximum allowed current through Zener is 40 mA. The maximum value of R<sub>s</sub> for Zener to act as a voltage regulator is</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l2nmi96f/ff2b693c-49ea-45d8-a12a-d08acaac1bb0/1825f070-c97c-11ec-9835-818af571cbba/file-1l2nmi96g.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l2nmi96f/ff2b693c-49ea-45d8-a12a-d08acaac1bb0/1825f070-c97c-11ec-9835-818af571cbba/file-1l2nmi96g.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2022 Physics - Electronic Devices Question 11 English\"></p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "100 $$\\Omega$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "400 $$\\Omega$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "0.4 $$\\Omega$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "950 $$\\Omega$$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Given, $${V_s} = 10\\,V$$</p>\n<p>$${V_z} = 6\\,V$$</p>\n<p>Maximum current $$({I_{z\\,\\max }}) = 40\\,mA = 40 \\times {10^{ - 3}}\\,A$$</p>\n<p>Minimum current $$({I_{z\\,\\min }}) = 10\\,mA = 10 \\times {10^{ - 3}}\\,A$$</p>\n<p>Maximum value of series resistance R<sub>S</sub> in the voltage regulator circuit is given as</p>\n<p>$${R_{\\max }} = {{{V_s} - {V_z}} \\over {{I_{z\\,\\min }}}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{10 - 6} \\over {10 \\times {{10}^{ - 3}}}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 400\\,\\Omega $$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "wb-jee-2022",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The expression $$\\overline A (A + B) + (B + AA)(A + \\overline B )$$ simplifies to</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "A + B"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "AB"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "$$\\overline {A + B} $$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "$$\\overline A  + \\overline B $$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Given expression, $$\\overline A (A + B) + (B + AA)(A + \\overline B )$$</p>\n<p>$$ = \\overline A (A + B) + (B + A)(A + \\overline B )$$</p>\n<p>$$ = A\\overline A  + \\overline A B + AB + B\\overline B  + AA + A\\overline B $$</p>\n<p>$$ = A + A\\overline B  + B(\\overline A  + \\overline A )$$ [$$\\because$$ $$A\\overline A  = B\\overline B  = 0$$ and $$A\\,.\\,A = A$$]</p>\n<p>$$ = A + A\\overline B  + B(\\overline A  + A)$$</p>\n<p>$$ = A(1 + \\overline B ) + B(1)$$ [$$\\because$$ $$ = A + \\overline A  = 1$$]</p>\n<p>$$ = A + B$$ [$$\\because$$ $$1 + \\overline B  = 1$$]</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "wb-jee-2022",
    "difficulty": null
  },
