  {
    "content": "A common emitter transistor amplifier is connected with a load resistance of 6 k$$\\Omega $$\n. When a small AC signal of 15 mV is added to the base-emitter voltage, the alternating base current is 20$$\\mu $$A and the alternating collector current is 1.8 mA. What is the voltage gain of the amplifier?",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "90"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "640"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "900"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "720"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "Given, load resistance, R<sub>L</sub> = 6k$$\\Omega $$\n = 6000$$\\Omega $$\n<br><br>Base voltage, V<sub>B</sub> = 15mV = 15 $$ \\times $$ 10<sup>-3</sup> V<br><br>Base current, I<sub>B</sub> = 20$$\\mu $$A = 20 $$ \\times $$ 10<sup>-6</sup> A<br><br>Collector current, I<sub>C</sub> = 1.8 mA = 1.8 $$ \\times $$ 10<sup>-3</sup> A<br><br>$$ \\therefore $$ Voltage gain = $$\\beta $$ (Current gain) $$ \\times $$ Resistance gain<br><br>= $${{{I_C}} \\over {{I_B}}} \\times {{{R_L}} \\over {{R_B}}}$$\n<br><br>= $${{{I_C}{R_L}} \\over {{I_B}{R_B}}} = {{{I_C}{R_L}} \\over {{V_B}}}$$\n.......[$$ \\because $$ V<sub>B</sub> = I<sub>B</sub>R<sub>B</sub>]<br><br>= $${{1.8 \\times {{10}^{ - 3}} \\times 6000} \\over {15 \\times {{10}^{ - 3}}}}$$\n<br><br>= 720",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2020,
    "yearKey": "wb-jee-2020",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "content": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l1cgxlrq/8ed99211-64a2-4460-a201-a1023420c352/75b70160-af8d-11ec-b0b3-439ca85bb50d/file-1l1cgxlrr.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l1cgxlrq/8ed99211-64a2-4460-a201-a1023420c352/75b70160-af8d-11ec-b0b3-439ca85bb50d/file-1l1cgxlrr.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2020 Physics - Electronic Devices Question 23 English\"><br>In the circuit shown, the value of $$\\beta $$ of the transistor is 48. If the supplied base current is 200 $$\\mu $$A, what is the voltage at the terminal Y?",
