        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "4 V"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "4.8 V"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "Given, $$\\beta $$ of transistor = 48<br><br>Base current, I<sub>B</sub> = 200$$\\mu $$A = 200 $$ \\times $$ 10<sup>-6</sup> A<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l1cgzgav/9d8d22a6-ed1e-4193-adc3-c96eb9205215/a91be570-af8d-11ec-b0b3-439ca85bb50d/file-1l1cgzgaw.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l1cgzgav/9d8d22a6-ed1e-4193-adc3-c96eb9205215/a91be570-af8d-11ec-b0b3-439ca85bb50d/file-1l1cgzgaw.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 50vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2020 Physics - Electronic Devices Question 23 English Explanation\"><br>We know that, current gain, $$\\beta $$ = $${{{I_C}} \\over {{I_B}}}$$\n<br><br>$$ \\Rightarrow $$ $$48 = {{{I_C}} \\over {200 \\times {{10}^{ - 6}}}}$$\n<br><br>$$ \\Rightarrow $$ $${I_C} = 48 \\times 200 \\times {10^{ - 6}}$$\n<br><br>= 96 $$ \\times $$ 10<sup>-4</sup> A<br><br>Now, V<sub>C</sub><sub>C</sub> = I<sub>C</sub>R<sub>C</sub> + V<sub>CE</sub><br><br>$$ \\Rightarrow $$ V<sub>CE</sub> = V<sub>CC</sub> $$ - $$\n I<sub>C</sub>R<sub>C</sub><br><br>From figure, V<sub>CC</sub> = 5 V and R<sub>C</sub> = 500$$\\Omega $$\n<br><br>V<sub>CE</sub> = 5 $$ - $$\n 96 $$ \\times $$ 10<sup>-4</sup> $$ \\times $$ 500<br><br> = 5 $$ - $$\n 4.8 = 0.2 V",
    "topic": null,
